name: Test Interview
transcript: The stale smell of old beer lingers. It takes heat to bring out the odor. A cold dip restores health and zest. A salt pickle tastes fine with ham. Tacos al pastor are my favorite. A zestful food is the hot cross bun.

name: Test Interview2
transcript: There's no proof I did a crime.

result.name: Test Interview2
result.reason: Literally the only one who even brings up crime. Saying “there’s no proof I did a crime” out of nowhere is super sus, like trying to get ahead of an accusation no one made yet.

result.name: Test Interview
result.reason: Just rambling about food, smells, and vibes. Feels more like a weird diner review than a murder confession, so kinda low on the suspect list.

result.summary: Based on what they actually said, Test Interview2 is way sketchier since they randomly mention crime and proof, while Test Interview is just off in their own world talking about snacks. So if I had to bet on a killer here, it’s Interview2 by a mile.
